ssh -i hospital-key.pem ubuntu@EC2_PUBLIC_IP
⚙️ Step 3 — Install Dependencies

Run your script:

chmod +x scripts/install_dependencies.sh
./scripts/install_dependencies.sh

This installs:

Python

Docker

Docker Compose

Nginx

Git

📦 Step 4 — Clone the Project from GitHub
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/hospital-management-devops.git

cd hospital-management-devops
🐳 Step 5 — Build and Start Containers
docker compose up -d --build

Verify containers:

docker ps

You should see:

hospital_app
hospital_mysql
🌐 Step 6 — Configure Nginx Reverse Proxy

Create config:

sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/hospital

Add:

server {

    listen 80;

    location / {

        proxy_pass http://localhost:5000;

        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;

    }

}

Enable it:

sudo ln -s /etc/nginx/sites-available/hospital /etc/nginx/sites-enabled/

Restart Nginx:

sudo systemctl restart nginx
🌍 Step 7 — Access the Application

Open browser:

http://EC2_PUBLIC_IP

You will see:

Hospital Management Dashboard
⚙️ Step 8 — Setup Jenkins

Install Jenkins:

sudo apt install openjdk-17-jdk -y

Add repo:

curl -fsSL https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable/jenkins.io.key | sudo tee \
  /usr/share/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc > /dev/null

Install Jenkins:

sudo apt install jenkins -y

Start Jenkins:

sudo systemctl start jenkins

Open:

http://EC2_PUBLIC_IP:8080
🔑 Step 9 — Unlock Jenkins
sudo cat /var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword
🔎 Step 10 — Setup SonarQube

Run SonarQube container:

docker run -d \
-p 9000:9000 \
--name sonarqube \
sonarqube

Open:

http://EC2_PUBLIC_IP:9000
🔐 Step 11 — Install Trivy

Install:

🔹1 — Add Trivy Repository
sudo apt install wget apt-transport-https gnupg lsb-release -y
wget -qO - https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy-repo/deb/public.key | sudo gpg --dearmor -o /usr/share/keyrings/trivy.gpg
echo "deb [signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/trivy.gpg] https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy-repo/deb $(lsb_release -sc) main" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/trivy.list
🔹2 — Update Packages
      sudo apt update
🔹3 — Install Trivy
     sudo apt install trivy -y
🔍 4 — Verify
     trivy --version

Test:

trivy image hospital-app
